  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "xorg-x11-server security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for xorg-x11-server is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "X.Org X11 X server\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nLocal attackers with a X connection able to provide PCX fonts to the X \nserver xorg-server before 21.2.24 and xwayland before 24.1.13 could \ncause a heap buffer overflow via SetFont due to missing glyph boundary checks.(CVE-2026-55999)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for xorg-x11-server is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of high. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "High",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "xorg-x11-server",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
